Title: Object: A View of Mount Ætna in Sicily (now called Mon Gibello)
Description: View of a smoking volcano from water in the foreground, with boat beside jagged rocks at left, one member of the crew climbing on the furled sails; after Richard Dalton. 1751 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Jean Baptiste Chatelain
Print made by: James Basire I
Curator's comments: Presumably a plate from Dalton's series 'Musaeum Graecaeum et Aegyptiacum, or Antiquities of Greece and Egypt' published in 1751.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Watkin Williams-Wynn, 8th Baronet
